content.description: Standing start in the center of the face, chuck to the horizontal from the arete, and try to smile while negotiating the thin slab above.
content.location: Located in the center of the cliff face.  Climb down either side of the cliff.

content.description: Standing start just left of the telephone pole on small holds, climb up and past the middle seam.
content.location: Located just left of the telephone pole.  Climb down either side of the cliff.

content.description: Starting near the graffiti, climb through the crimps, then up and around the overhang.
content.location: This route starts near the graffiti ten feet left of the telephone pole. Climb down either side of the cliff.

content.description: Tall low angle slabs on some pretty solid rock.  The Shit Hole holds two good lines and one that's alright.  These routes are on the brink of top roping and bouldering.  You decide.  The right most route, not so uniquely named 'shit hole', a double-entendre hinting at both the type of holds and early climbers' feelings on the crag itself, makes this place worth the trip.
